+{"id":"frankenpandas-gwa2","title":"fp-frame: DataFrame.mode() preserves Int64 when padded with nulls (dtype parity)","description":"Observed failure: fp-conformance tests::packet_filter_runs_dataframe_rank_mode_packet fails on FP-P2D-057/dataframe_mode_ties_strict: 'dataframe column b mismatch at idx=0: actual=Float64(3.0), expected=Int64(3)'.\n\nFixture: columns a=[1,1,2,2] (2 tied modes) and b=[3,3,3,4] (1 mode). max_modes=2, so column b gets padded with Null(NaN) to match. Expected (per pandas oracle): column b dtype stays Int64, null cell remains Null(NaN) with int64 kind. Actual: fp-frame widens to Float64.\n\nRoot: crates/fp-frame/src/lib.rs:411 fn mode_output_dtype returns DType::Float64 when saw_missing || saw_int is true. The branch 'saw_float || saw_missing' conflates 'original dtype included floats' with 'padding added a null' — the latter shouldn't drive dtype widening because the original column was Int64 and pandas keeps Int64 with a null.\n\nFix: separate the padding-induced saw_missing from genuine float widening. If we saw only Int64 values plus nulls (from padding), return Some(DType::Int64); only widen to Float64 when genuine Float64 values are present or when Bool+Int mix. Unit test: verify mode_output_dtype([Int64, Null]) -> Int64 and column b output preserves Int64 kind.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-22T04:42:35.315784398Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T04:42:40.747795883Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
